      • CREATE_USER

        public static final CommunicationMessage CREATE_USER
        User createUser messages. CREATE_USER is sent by the client to the server to create a new User, the server will process the request and send a CREATE_USER_OK or CREATE_USER_FAILED in case of success or failure. USER_JOIN_WAITING_ROOM is sent by the client when a CREATE_USER_OK is received, in order to join a waiting room or a game and a USER_JOINED_WAITING_ROOM confirmation message will be sent. Arguments:

      • DAMAGE_TO_MAKE

        public static final CommunicationMessage DAMAGE_TO_MAKE
        Damage apply message. DAMAGE_TO_MAKE is sent from the client to the server to notify the selection of the damage that has to be applied to the other players. LAST_DAMAGE acts just like DAMAGE_TO_MAKE, but signals that it will be the last damage of the weapon to be done. DAMAGE_DONE is sent from the server to the client to notify that damage has been done LAST_DAMAGE_DONE is sent from the server to the client to notify that the process of using the weapon is over. It has got only the weapon as argument. Arguments: , ,

      • TAGBACK_CHOSEN

        public static final CommunicationMessage TAGBACK_CHOSEN
        Tagback powerup using messages. TAGBACK_CHOSEN is sent from the client to the server to notify the selection of a powerup. WILL_CHOOSE_TAGBACK is sent from the server to the client to notify the possibility of tagging back. WONT_USE_TAGBACK is sent from the client to the server to notify that no tagging back will happen. Arguments: for CHOSEN, for WILL_CHOOSE

      • UPDATE_SITUATION

        public static final CommunicationMessage UPDATE_SITUATION
        View update messages. UPDATE_SITUATION is sent from the server to the client to notify that some other player has done something in his turn. UPDATE_ALL is sent from the server to the client to notify any change. DISPLAY_FINAL_FRENZY is sent from the server to the client to notify that final frenzy game has begun. Arguments: none Arguments:

        public static final CommunicationMessage CHECK_DEATHS_AFTER_TURN
